    "[nav]: Wikipedia.org serves as a global portal leading to specific language Wikipedias and Wikimedia Foundation resources. The information architecture is very flat and focus-oriented.",
    "[auth]: Entry points are primarily found after navigating from the global portal to a specific language edition (e.g., English Wikipedia).",
    "[commerce]: Wikipedia itself is a non-profit encyclopedia. However, it hosts a commercial merchandise store (store.wikimedia.org) and a donation platform (donate.wikimedia.org) that both feature commerce-like checkout flows.",
